---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Nanato Studio, a personal technical site for manuals, notes, projects, and small tools."
  pageClass="entry-page about-page"
>
  <section class="about-hero page-enter" aria-labelledby="about-title">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 id="about-title">A quiet technical studio for work that should stay understandable.</h1>
      <p>
        Nanato Studio collects project manuals, engineering notes, and lightweight experiments in one public surface.
        The goal is not to mirror a documentation tree; it is to make the work easier to revisit.
      </p>
    </div>
    <img
      src="/assets/aiformula/images/landing-hero.svg"
      alt="Abstract technical interface preview"
      width="1200"
      height="780"
      loading="lazy"
      decoding="async"
    />
  </section>

  <section class="about-principles page-enter page-enter--delay-1" aria-label="Studio principles">
    <article>
      <span>01</span>
      <h2>Manuals over memory</h2>
      <p>Durable reference material lives with projects and docs so context does not disappear after a sprint ends.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span>02</span>
      <h2>Notes stay separate</h2>
      <p>Writing belongs in the Blog when it is reflective, temporary, or editorial rather than reference-heavy.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span>03</span>
      <h2>Projects get shape</h2>
      <p>Project hubs connect manuals, experiments, and future apps without forcing every link into the header.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="studio-section studio-section--split page-enter page-enter--delay-2">
    <div class="studio-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Start reading</p>
      <h2>Use Blogs when you want the thinking behind the work.</h2>
      <p>Blogs stay editorial, while project pages and docs carry longer-lived manuals and reference material.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/blog/">Open Blogs</a>
    </div>
    <div class="studio-panel studio-panel--dark">
      <p class="eyebrow">Current focus</p>
      <h2>AI Formula is the strongest project manual today.</h2>
      <p>It remains available at its original docs route, with project context surfaced through the Projects hub.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/projects/">Open Projects</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
